RIYADH: Saudi Arabia’s King Salman and Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman sent cables of condolences Saturday to the emir of Kuwait on the death of Sheikh Saud Abdullah Saud Al-Malik Al-Sabah. The king sent his “deepest and sincerest condolences” to Emir Sheikh Nawaf Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah and to the family of the deceased. Prince Mohammed sent cables of condolences to both the emir of Kuwait and his Crown Prince Sheikh Meshal Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah, praying that God have mercy on the deceased.